                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d156">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Conger</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-01-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 26, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Hay instructs Mr. Conger to enter energetic protest against the forfeiture
                    of the Canton-Hankau Railroad concession. Great sacrifices have been made by the
                    American proprietors to regain entire control of it, and the Government of the
                    United States can not acquiesce in such an act of spoliation as the forfeiture
                    of the concession would be.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
